article.headline: Ark.-Little Rock 75, Stetson 50
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Solomon Bozeman scored 16 points and had seven assists to lead Arkansas-Little Rock over Stetson 75-50 on Thursday night in the final round of the Las Vegas Holiday Hoops Classic. Alex Garcia-Mendoza and Matt Mouzy each had 11 points for the Trojans (8-6). Daylon Guy added 10 points for Arkansas-Little Rock, which shot 24 of 44 (55 percent) and 12 of 20 (60 percent) from 3-point range. Jermol Paul led the Hatters (3-9) with 11 points, while Ridge Graham added nine. Except for the early stages of the first half, the Trojans led throughout, once building a 41-23 edge thanks to shooting 14 of 21 from the field and 8 of 10 from 3-point range. Arkansas-Little Rock led 42-27 at halftime. The Hatters cut it to 45-34 but got no closer as the lead grew to 31. The Trojans finished the Classic 2-2, while the Hatters were 0-4.
